{"lemma":"سِرْحان","slug":"سِرْحان","root":"س.ر.ح","root_slug":"س-ر-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19514"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wolf","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lion","tags":["dialectal","obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"absent-minded, distracted"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From سَرَحَ (saraḥa, “to go out between dawn and sunrise”) + ـَان (-ān). From the root س ر ح (s r ḥ)."},"ipa":["/sir.ħaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19514","headword_ar":"سِرْحَانٌ","root":"srH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolaAnN","text_ar":"فِعْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an augmentative letter, (Sb, S,) from the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraHa","text_ar":"سَرَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wolf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siroHaAlN","text_ar":"سِرْحَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Yaakoob, K;) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siroHaAnapN","text_ar":"سِرْحَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siroHaAlahN","text_ar":"سِرْحَالَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,) in the dial. of Hudheyl: (S, O:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAHiynu","text_ar":"سَرَاحِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAHK","text_ar":"سَرَاحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siraAHN","text_ar":"سِرَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, L, K,) but the last not remembered to have been heard by Az. (L.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"saqaTa AlEa$aA='u bihi EalaY siroHaAni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The evening-meal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. the seeking for it,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light, upon a wolf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Meyd:) accord. to A'Obeyd, it originated from a man's going forth to seek the eveningmeal, and falling upon a wolf, which devoured him: accord. to As, from the like accident to a beast: accord. to IAar, from a man's being slain by another man, named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siroHaAn","text_ar":"سِرْحَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is applied to the seeking an object of want that leads one to destruction. (Meyd. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 599: but the name there written “ Hasahah ” is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huzolap","text_ar":"هُزْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; accord. to Meyd, the father, but accord. to the O, the brother, of Sirhán.]) ―         -b2-  Hence, (Mgh, Msb,) i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iroHaAnu","text_ar":"السِّرْحَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ the wolf, ” or, as some say, “ the lion, ” (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*anabu","text_ar":"ذَنَبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iroHaAni","text_ar":"السِّرْحَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The false dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, K, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [A term nearly agreeing with the Greek"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"λυκόφως","text_ar":"λυκόφως","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iroHaAnu","text_ar":"السِّرْحَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siroHaAnN","text_ar":"سِرْحَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a wateringtrough or tank: (O, K:) pl. as above. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["Sb","S","TA","Ks","O","Msb","K","A","L","Meyd","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}